Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportConnectivity(25.10)                            reportConnectivity(25.10)

Name
       reportConnectivity  -  Reports  the  connectivity of pins including I/O
       pins, partition pins, hpins, hterms, hinstterms, and instterms

Syntax
       reportConnectivity

       [-help]

       <pinName>

       [-level <integer>]

       [-pinOnly]

       Reports the connectivity of pins including I/O  pins,  partition  pins,
       hpins, hterms, hinstterms, and instterms.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each reportConnectivity command parameter.  For  a
              detailed  description  of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command: man reportConnectivity

       -level <integer>
              Specifies the number of levels to be printed in the report.

              Note: The level cannot be set to 0.

              Default: 1

              Data_type: int, optional

       <pinName>
              Specifies the name of the pin whose connectivity is  to  be  re-
              ported.

              Data_type: string, required

       -pinOnly
              Prints  a  concise connectivity report of partition pins and I/O
              pins from the start point

              Data_type: bool, optional

       The connectivity report uses the following symbols:

       -->    When going inside child hinst

       <--    When going to parent hinst

              |" When the level of both pins is same

       assign When there is assign statement in netlist

Example
              * The following command reports the connectivity of  the  speci-
                fied ibias pin.

                reportConnectivity ibias

                The following is the resulting report.

                  1 io       input  -        ibias

                  2 hterm    input  -->      IOPADS_INST/ibias

              * The  following  command reports the connectivity of the speci-
                fied ibias pin up to level 2:

                 reportConnectivity ibias -level 2

                The following is the resulting report.

                  1 io       input  -        ibias

                  2 hterm    input  -->      IOPADS_INST/ibias

                  3 instterm input  -->      IOPADS_INST/Pibiasip/PAD

              * The following command reports the connectivity of  the  speci-
                fied ibias pin with a concise connectivity report of partition
                pins and I/O pins :

                reportConnectivity ibias -level 2 -pinOnly

                The following is the resulting report.

                  1 io       input  -          ibias

                  2 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[15]

                  3 io       output assign     tdigit_flag

                  4 io       output assign     tdigit[7]

                  5 io       output assign     tdigit[3]

                  6 io       output assign     tdigit[4]

                  7 io       output assign     tdigit[5]

                  8 io       output assign     tdigit[6]

                  9 io       output assign     tdigit[2]

                 10 io       output assign     tdigit[1]

                 11 io       output assign     tdigit[0]

                 12 io       output assign     scan_out_2

                 13 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[14]

                 14 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[10]

                 15 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[1]

                 16 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[0]

                 17 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[2]

                 18 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[4]

                 19 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[3]

                 20 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[7]

                 21 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[6]

                 22 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[5]

                 23 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[8]

                 24 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[11]

                 25 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[9]

                 26 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[12]

                 27 io       output assign     port_pad_data_out[13]

                 28 io       output assign     scan_out_1

                 29 io       output assign     vcop

                 30 io       output assign     vcom

              * The  following  command reports the connectivity of the speci-
                fied i1/p1_buff2/A instterm up to level 10:

                reportConnectivity i1/p1_buff2/A -level 10

                The following is the resulting report.

                  1 instterm input  -        i1/p1_buff2/A

                  2 instterm output |          i1/p1_buff2/Y

                  3 hterm    input  |            i1/p01/in

                  4 hterm    output assign         i1/p01/out

                  5 ptnpin   output <--              i1/out

                  6 instterm input  |                  top_buff2/A

                  7 instterm output |                    top_buff2/Y

                  8 instterm input  |                      top_buff3/A

                  9 instterm output |                        top_buff3/Y

                 10 io       output <--                        out

              * The following command reports the connectivity of  the  speci-
                fied i1/p01/out hinstterm up to level 10:

                reportConnectivity i1/p01/out -level 10

                The following is the resulting report.

                  1 hterm    output -        i1/p01/out

                  2 ptnpin   output <--        i1/out

                  3 instterm input  |            top_buff2/A

                  4 instterm output |              top_buff2/Y

                  5 instterm input  |                top_buff3/A

                  6 instterm output |                  top_buff3/Y

                  7 io       output <--                  out

              * The  following  command reports the connectivity of the speci-
                fied out I/O pin up to level -5:

                reportConnectivity out -level -5

                The following is the resulting report.

                  1 io       output -                out

                  2 instterm output -->            top_buff3/Y

                  3 instterm input  |            top_buff3/A

                  4 instterm output |          top_buff2/Y

                  5 instterm input  |        top_buff2/A

                  6 ptnpin   output |      i1/out

